title: If the display property of an item is set to 'none', it doesn't take effect in new pdf emitter.
OB: When the display property of an item is set to 'none' in the new pdf emitter, the label is still visible when previewed in PDF.
EB: Expected result: The label should disappear when the display property of an item is set to 'none' in the new pdf emitter. Actual result: The label is still visible in the PDF preview.
SR:
1. Open the new pdf emitter.
2. Set the display property of an item to 'none'.
3. Preview the PDF.
4. Verify that the label of the item is still visible.
